<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-471-035  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 471 035.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  Oct 1990 v15 n10 p133(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Catch the Mac's screen with MediaTracks. (Software Review)(Farallon Computing Inc's presentation development and playbacksoftware) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Thompson, Tom.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Farallon Computing Inc's $295 MediaTracks is a useful, easy-to-useand powerful software package for making software demonstrationsby recording and playing back an application executing on a AppleMacintosh computer.andP;  The software includes a ScreenRecorder deskaccessory (DA) that captures the sequence of displays on the Macscreen to a 'virtual tape file,' an editor that can also add soundand interactive user controls, Preferences menu, ScreenSaver andSoundEdit capabilities.andP;  The software uses a'videotape/film-splicing analogy' that enables the user to rapidlyedit the demonstrations, including splicing out errors, adding innew sessions or adjusting the playback speed of various portionsof the tape.andP;  Test of a MediaTracks demonstration showed it towork well over a variety of Macintosh computers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Farallon Computing Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)MediaTracks (Multimedia software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationSpecificationsProgram Development ToolsSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>